The impact of the <TIMEX3 tid="t1" type="DATE" value="2010">2010</TIMEX3> oil spill in the Gulf of Mexico .
While oil company BP was trying to stop the oil leaking off the coast of America , the damage to the environment was getting worse and worse .
At least 27 million litres of crude oil have flowed into the water since the pipe started leaking in <TIMEX3 tid="t4" type="DATE" value="2010-04">April 2010</TIMEX3> , threatening wildlife such as birds .
There were a number of attempts to plug the leak .
Presenters Sonali and Ricky find out more from Grahame Madge of the RSPB .
